Adapted components
------------------
- Event flags, layouts, orders, and state accounting
- L2 hash-map and ROI-vector market-depth models
- Asset, fee, latency, and queue models
- Local and exchange processors and latency-aware order buses
- Event scheduler, multi-asset backtest loop, readers, and recorder
- NPY/NPZ event ingestion concepts and core behavioral tests

The C++ implementation, CMake packaging, deterministic example, benchmark,
automation, and presentation assets were produced for this independent port.
The underlying architecture and algorithms originated in HftBacktest. The MIT
license in LICENSE applies to the port and retains the upstream notice.
